On 5/20/03 8:24 AM, "Dan Soiney" <soineydg(-at-)milwaukee.k12.wi.us> wrote:

> On the subject of temp. senders, how difficult is it to remove the FI Head
> temp sender?  I've never changed this, and have owned my bus since 1989.  I
> am worried it is stuck in the head, and will booger the hole when I try to
> get it out. Any tips??

The hole is very small and I didn't have a problem replacing my original
sender.

The hardest part is getting in there with a tool because I couldn't get it
out with my fingers. One of those 13mm ratcheting box end wrenches works
wonders.

